abstract: Oil prices trickled a fraction lower on Tuesday but remained near a three-month high as investors kept the faith with hopes that a fully fledged U.S.-China trade deal is in the pipeline, set to stoke oil demand in the world's biggest economies.
snippet: Oil prices trickled a fraction lower on Tuesday but remained near a three-month high as investors kept the faith with hopes that a fully fledged U.S.-China trade deal is in the pipeline, set to stoke oil demand in the world's biggest economies.
lead_paragraph: SINGAPORE — Oil prices trickled a fraction lower on Tuesday but remained near a three-month high as investors kept the faith with hopes that a fully fledged U.S.-China trade deal is in the pipeline, set to stoke oil demand in the world's biggest economies.
headline_main: Oil Poised Near Three-Month Highs on U.S.-China Trade Hopes, Supply Cuts
headline_print_headline: Oil Poised Near Three-Month Highs on U.S.-China Trade Hopes, Supply Cuts

abstract: The scale of Boris Johnson's election victory on Thursday may be enough to draw back billions of pounds of investment that have sidestepped UK stocks for years over Brexit, mirroring the U.S. market surge seen after Donald Trump's election three years ago.
snippet: The scale of Boris Johnson's election victory on Thursday may be enough to draw back billions of pounds of investment that have sidestepped UK stocks for years over Brexit, mirroring the U.S. market surge seen after Donald Trump's election three y...
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The scale of Boris Johnson's election victory on Thursday may be enough to draw back billions of pounds of investment that have sidestepped UK stocks for years over Brexit, mirroring the U.S. market surge seen after Donald Trump's election three years ago.
headline_main: UK Stocks May Move From Brexit Fear to 'Fear of Missing Out'
headline_print_headline: UK Stocks May Move From Brexit Fear to 'Fear of Missing Out'

abstract: The so-called Phase One trade deal between Washington and Beijing has been "absolutely completed," a top White House adviser said on Monday, adding that U.S. exports to China will double under the agreement.
snippet: The so-called Phase One trade deal between Washington and Beijing has been "absolutely completed," a top White House adviser said on Monday, adding that U.S. exports to China will double under the agreement.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The so-called Phase One trade deal between Washington and Beijing has been "absolutely completed," a top White House adviser said on Monday, adding that U.S. exports to China will double under the agreement.
headline_main: Kudlow: U.S.-China Deal 'Absolutely' Done, U.S. Exports to China Will Double
headline_print_headline: Kudlow: U.S.-China Deal 'Absolutely' Done, U.S. Exports to China Will Double

abstract: U.S. special envoy for North Korea, Stephen Biegun, urged Pyongyang on Monday to return offers of talks, dismissing leader Kim Jong Un's year-end deadline while highlighting Washington's willingness to discuss "all issues of interest".
snippet: U.S. special envoy for North Korea, Stephen Biegun, urged Pyongyang on Monday to return offers of talks, dismissing leader Kim Jong Un's year-end deadline while highlighting Washington's willingness to discuss "all issues of interest".
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — U.S. special envoy for North Korea, Stephen Biegun, urged Pyongyang on Monday to return offers of talks, dismissing leader Kim Jong Un's year-end deadline while highlighting Washington's willingness to discuss "all issues of interest".
headline_main: U.S. Envoy Biegun to North Korea: 'We're Here, You Know How to Reach Us'
headline_print_headline: U.S. Envoy Biegun to North Korea: 'We're Here, You Know How to Reach Us'

abstract: The House will vote on the impeachment of President Donald Trump this week after spending the past three months investigating the president's dealings in Ukraine and deciding whether his behavior was grave enough to qualify as high crimes and misdemeanors.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House will vote on the impeachment of President Donald Trump this week after spending the past three months investigating the president's dealings in Ukraine and deciding whether his behavior was grave enough to qualify as high crimes and misdemeanors.
headline_main: House Vote, and On to the Senate: What's Next in Impeachment

abstract: As near-certain impeachment closes in on him, President Donald Trump raged at his accusers, the Democrats. In the process, he offered a highly selective account of the testimony of a damning witness and misrepresented the facts of a phone call with Ukraine's president at the heart of the constitutional showdown.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As near-certain impeachment closes in on him, President Donald Trump raged at his accusers, the Democrats. abstract: Seven Democratic presidential candidates will stand on stage this week in Los Angeles, a pool of survivors who have withstood almost a year on the campaign trail, sustained attacks from rivals in both major political parties and five rounds of high-pressure debates.

lead_paragraph: CLINTON, Iowa — Seven Democratic presidential candidates will stand on stage this week in Los Angeles, a pool of survivors who have withstood almost a year on the campaign trail, sustained attacks from rivals in both major political parties and five rounds of high-pressure debates.
headline_main: Turbulence Shakes Democrats Going Into Final Debate of 2019

abstract: Growth in China's industrial and retail sectors beat expectations in November, as government support propped up demand in the world's second-largest economy and amid easing trade hostilities with Washington.
snippet: Growth in China's industrial and retail sectors beat expectations in November, as government support propped up demand in the world's second-largest economy and amid easing trade hostilities with Washington.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — Growth in China's industrial and retail sectors beat expectations in November, as government support propped up demand in the world's second-largest economy and amid easing trade hostilities with Washington.
headline_main: China's Factory, Retail Sectors Shine as Trade Tensions Thaw
headline_print_headline: China's Factory, Retail Sectors Shine as Trade Tensions Thaw

abstract: Stephen E. Biegun appealed to the North to return to dialogue on denuclearization. “Let’s get this done,” he said.
snippet: Stephen E. Biegun appealed to the North to return to dialogue on denuclearization. “Let’s get this done,” he said.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — The top United States envoy on North Korea warned on Monday that if Pyongyang conducted a major weapons test in the coming days as feared, it would be “most unhelpful,” as Washington tried to de-escalate tensions with the country.
